  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed residential use and lack of noise mitigation measures would result in unreasonable restrictions being placed upon established noise and other nuisance-generating uses, threatening their viability and opportunity to continue growth as established night time venues. As such, the proposed change of use fails to comply with Policy D13 of the London Plan (2021).&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to contribute towards the Carbon Offset Fund,&amp;nbsp; would fail to meet the London Objective of being a zero-carbon city by 2050, contrary to policies SI 2 (Minimising greenhouse gas emissions) of the London Plan (2021), policy&amp;nbsp; LP55 (Mitigating Climate Change) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed roof terrace and associated works, by reason of its location, means of access/egress and lack of sufficient overlooking mitigation measures, would result in a loss of privacy for neighbouring dwellings contrary to LP2 &#x27;Development and Amenity&#x27; of the Hackney local plan and D6 &#x27;Housing Quality and Standards&#x27; of the London plan as well as the guidelines Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure car-free housing, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable modes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the surrounding area, contrary to policies T6 (Car Parking) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure a contribution towards affordable housing fails to deliver the maximum reasonable amount of affordable housing and is therefore contrary to Policy H4 (Delivering affordable housing) of the London Plan (2021) and Policy LP13 (Affordable housing) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed loss of Class E office floor space within a designated Priority Office Area (POA), Central Activity Zone (CAZ) and the Shoreditch Area Action Plan, would harm the vitality and function of the POA and CAZ, contrary to the NPPF(2021), Policies SD4(The Central Activities Zone), SD5 (Offices, other strategic functions and residential development in the CAZ) and E1 (Offices) of the London Plan (2021) and Policies LP26( Employment Land and Floorspace) and LP27(Protecting and Promoting Office Floorspace in the Borough) of Hackney’s Local Plan (2020).&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of inadequate internal GIAs for flats B and C would result in a substandard level of accommodation as a result of insufficient floorspace and privacy impacts contrary to policy LP17&amp;nbsp; of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020) and policy D6 of the London Plan (2021)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development has failed to make suitable provision for the storage and collection of waste contrary to LP57 of the Hackney Local Plan.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development by virtue of not providing any cycle storage fails to promote sustainable transport within the Borough contrary to LP42 of the Hackney Local Plan(2020) and Policy T5 of the London Plan (2021).&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;Insufficient information has been provided to demonstrate that the alterations to the shopfront would safeguard the special interest of the listed building and character and appearance of the conservation area, as such the development is contrary to Policy HC1 (Heritage Conservation and Growth) of the London Plan (2021) and Policy LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020).&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
